snippet.textDisplay:
I really love the meticulousness of this beautiful dish as it is superbly executed by the virtuous Chris Morocco! 😍💪🏽 🍽💖
Just one question: where are the herbs and spices at?! I'd love to at the very least add in some dried Italian herbs mix to the ragù. At which point in the process could I best include this?
Then I'd also like to put some more vegetables in it to make it a dish that also checks off all the boxes on the nutrients list for my dinner and also just because I find it tasty! ☺️ I was thinking about spinach🍃, more(!) carrot🥕, (mixed) mushrooms🍄 (if seasonal), courgette🥒 (zucchini), (aubergine) eggplant🍆 (love the stuff!) and perhaps broccoli🥦. Does BA have any suggestions or tips or tricks for adding more vegetables? I was also thinking about splitting the ragù in two parts and pots, making one pot the BA's OG ground meat precisely to the every pinch of salt and one pot with tasty and nutricious veggies in the tomato, wine and milk sauce but then also maybe frying half of the batch of meatballs in the pot for the veggie-sauce for flavour development. Then I could build the lasagna one layer ground-meat ragù, one layer rich veggie-sauce, alternating. Ideas?... 🧀🍽🍷
snippet.textOriginal:

Just one question: *where* are the *herbs* and spices *at?!* I'd love to *at the very least* add in some dried Italian herbs mix to the ragù. At which point in the process could I best include this? 
Then I'd also like to put some more vegetables in it to make it a dish that also checks off all the boxes on the nutrients list for my dinner and also just because I find it tasty! ☺️ I was thinking about spinach🍃, more(!) carrot🥕, (mixed) mushrooms🍄 (if seasonal), courgette🥒 (zucchini), (aubergine) eggplant🍆 (love the stuff!) and perhaps broccoli🥦. Then I could build the lasagna one layer ground-meat ragù, one layer rich veggie-sauce, alternating. Ideas?...  🧀🍽🍷
